      "writtenOn": "2020-08-26T17:02:10Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Yes, it looks like that BuildSteps._pre_put_hook() has an assertion for it, and perhaps, BuildSteps in go could have the same check with PropertyLoadSaver interface.\n\nhttps://source.chromium.org/chromium/infra/infra/+/master:appengine/cr-buildbucket/model.py;l\u003d438-442;drc\u003d1cfba983de10022ef4afb88c017dbd8725856d31\n\nbut also, we\u0027d like to check the byte size during the validation process, I believe.\nHow about FromProto() checks the zipped []byte size with this constant again after zipping. Then, validateUpdate() doesn\u0027t need to run the size check, and this constant doesn\u0027t need to be exposed.\n\n--------------------\nQ. was there any reason why the size of the zipped bytes were checked again inside validate_steps(), not in model.write_steps()? for example, BuildSteps with zipped steps larger than 1e6 is allowed some places, whereas it is not allowed in some other places.",
      "parentUuid": "9089a42e_1a058cd5",
      "revId": "28b34bdb539108b18add01efea727ffdb2ba0e0c",
