      "message": "this looks like an invitation for a problem in the future.\nOne may use this context to make an RPC which we don\u0027t want here.\n\nalso I had to look into the impl to make sure does not an RPC.\n\nFromProto uses context only to generate a datastore key that then used in the error message, so the FromProto doesn\u0027t really need a context. Would you simplify that func to remove context param?\n\nthen we don\u0027t need context param in validateSteps (it is a bit weird to have context in validate* functions)",
